{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, we argue that the advertising loads are symmetric in equilibrium.",
    "To see this, consider the map ψ: [0, 1] → [0, 1] that maps left-wing advertiser's load, α (L), to advertising load of the right-wing party, α (R), that would maximize the gains for the right-wing party from advertising.",
    "Generically, this map is well-defined (there is a single global maximum, see Ott and Yorke (2005)), continuous and maps a convex set onto itself, and thus by Brouwer's theorem has a fixed point ψ(α * /2) = α * /2 for some total advertising load α * > 0.",
    "By symmetry, when the right-wing party is advertising at α * /2, it is also a best response for the left-wing party to advertise at α * /2.",
    "Thus, the proposed contract from the platform to the firm in equilibrium involves (α (L) *, α (R) *) = (α * /2, α * /2)."
  ]
}